Former Machakos Senator Johnson Muthama was arrested during the Msambweni by-election on Tuesday for allegedly causing a disturbance.
Mr Muthama, who is Deputy President William Ruto's ally, was apprehended at the Jomo Kenyatta Primary School polling station.
Former Mombasa Senator Hassan Omar confirmed the arrest, saying police officers took the senator from Kwale to Mombasa County.



