"We are keeping vigilance because we know our opponents are bribing voters and can't win this election fairly," he claimed.





Former Machakos Senator Johnson Muthama is pictured in a police vehicle following his arrest during the Msambweni by-election in Kwale County on December 15, 2020.
Photo credit: Courtesy


Police sources said Mr Muthama was taken to Port Police Station.
Mr Muthama, Mr Omar and former Kakamega Senator Boni Khalwale have been leading campaigns for independent candidate Feisal Bader.
Mr Bader's team has alleged harassment by police officers while claiming that people in the Orange Democratic Movement (ODM) team are allowed to roam freely inside polling stations.



